<subSubSection id="80CE6533C836443DDFB3FE8963C228A4" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C86B36B8C836443DDFB3FE8963C228A4" blockId="17.[151,1437,350,771]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">
<emphasis id="FAA0EAAAC836443DDFB3FE8962302830" bold="true" box="[151,295,350,375]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">Diagnosis. S</emphasis>
ubcylindrical body; dorsal and ventral region covered with sparse yellow pubescence; posterior angle of pronotum with short and oblique carina; scutellum carinate; elytra with anterior suboval tubercle, covered with strong rugosities, posterior half of elytra without tubercles; longitudinal median carina of ventrite 5 with four small teeth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
